<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911210-0058</DOCNO><DOCID>911210-0058.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Meritor Savings Bank:   Meritor Savings Is Selling   Sandamp;L Unit Based in Florida</HL><DATE>12/10/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C10</SO><CO>   MTOR</CO><MS>FINANCIAL (FIN)</MS><IN>SAVINGS AND LOANS, THRIFTS (SAL)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>EARNINGS PROJECTIONS (ERP)ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>FLORIDA (FL)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PENNSYLVANIA (PA)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Meritor Savings Bank said it agreed to sell its savingsand loan subsidiary, Meritor Savings F.A., to WMG HoldingCo., formed by a group of individual investors.   Philadelphia-based Meritor declined to identify theinvestors. Under the agreement, WMG Holding will pay about$35 million for the subsidiary, which is based in WinterHaven, Fla., and operates 43 branches in central Florida andWashington, D.C. It has $1.3 billion in assets, said Meritor.The sale will result in a $28 million non-cash charge in thefourth quarter, related primarily to the write-off of goodwill associated with the unit, Meritor said.</LP><TEXT>   Meritor, which will have $5 billion in assets after thesale of its subsidiary, said the sale will improve regulatorycapital levels and help its plan to shed operations outsideof its core banking franchise.</TEXT></DOC>